title: Google\Cloud\Dataflow\V1beta3\ListJobMessagesRequest
name: ListJobMessagesRequest
description:
Request to list job messages.

Up to max_results messages will be returned in the time range specified starting with the oldest messages first. If no time range is specified the results with start with the oldest message.

Generated from protobuf message google.dataflow.v1beta3.ListJobMessagesRequest

params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.minimum_importance
params.description: Filter to only get messages with importance >= level

params.name: data.page_size
params.description: If specified, determines the maximum number of messages to return. If unspecified, the service may choose an appropriate default, or may return an arbitrarily large number of results.

params.name: data.page_token
params.description: If supplied, this should be the value of next_page_token returned by an earlier call. This will cause the next page of results to be returned.

params.name: data.start_time
params.description: If specified, return only messages with timestamps >= start_time. The default is the job creation time (i.e. beginning of messages).

params.name: data.end_time
params.description: Return only messages with timestamps < end_time. The default is now (i.e. return up to the latest messages available).

params.name: data.location
params.description: The [regional endpoint] (https://cloud.google.com/dataflow/docs/concepts/regional-endpoints) that contains the job specified by job_id.
